node.text:
After Dinner…

There is nothing like summer evenings out on our back deck, though they were few this July with unpredictable and uncommon weather!

We added the firetowers from @planikafires this summer and not only do they set the mood, they keep us warm too! (Swipe!)

These have been restocked and I got a 10% off code for you with free shipping!

Use 10SilverShed if you are thinking of ordering!

I’m adding the link in my bio and will add a swipe up in my stories as well!
#welivehere

node.text:
Eventide:
(The period between afternoon and nighttime: dusk, eve, evening, sunset, nightfall, twilight.)

The opposite is Daybreak.

Together, they are my candle scents! 

Guess what? 
They’re back in the full size set, Daybreak and Eventide! (SWIPE!)

They are quintessential Cape Cod fragrances, developed to remind me of sunrise and sunset here by the beach.

Daybreak is a rich blend of sweet grass, violet, bamboo and bergamot.

Eventide is a moodier scent, a blend of birchwood, cypress, rose petals and lily.

These are a limited pour!
And if you are still on the fence and want to try them in small batch first, we have a limited amount of travel sets available as well!

(They are all natural, soy based made using essential oils and they are long lasting! They come beautifully wrapped and make a lovely gift!)
We can also ship worldwide!

I put the link in my bio and will share in stories as well!

node.text:
Fading Fast…

That’s the way it is with Hydrangeas, though they are pretty along the way.

I know I said “Less is More” a few days ago, but I’m fickle.🤭
They look so happy together in our back hall! 
(SWIPE!)

A few years ago I got a snarky comment about this cabinet being “ghetto”. I still laugh about that because I couldn’t love it more.💙 (I got it at Brimfield and Michele @vintagefurniturereclaimed tweaked it just perfectly and made it shine!💙)

So many of you asked about my little glass bottles in the boxes I shared in stories yesterday, I’m pulling a bunch of good options together and will share in stories tomorrow!
#welivehere

node.text:
From Morning ‘Til Night…

We’ve been on a weather-rollercoaster for weeks now🙄!
Foggy and cold with the heat on, then hot and muggy with the A/C on. At the first sign of sun we run and open all the windows and doors for fresh air.
And that’s just in one day!

I make sure we are prepared for all of it with soft and airy layers in our guest room! #ad

For our summer bedroom refresh, I’ve partnered with @bollandbranch to lift this room to luxurious! I’m using their beautiful Linen Stripe duvet cover and shams (color “Shore”) in here, and I’ve paired them with their 100% organic cotton Signature Embroidered Sheets in pure, crisp white! Then, for an extra layer I added the Waffle Bed Blanket. And I like to keep a light throw in here in case we open those doors to the porch in the evening and it's a little breezy! This one is the Sweater Knit Throw Blanket (in Birch White). For a finishing touch I chose the Mattelassé Window Pane accent pillow!🤍

I love all of these organic, lightweight layers together. For me, the softer and wrinklier the better! I want my guests to have a memorable visit with us and while the weather cannot be relied on, the coziness of our guest room remains constant!

Swipe through to see how the light in the room changes with the weather throughout the day- but those bed linens? Always inviting!

You can use my promo code:
SANDRA20 to receive a 20% off your order! (See site for details!)

And, I’ve shared more details with links in my stories!

node.text:
It’s Hydrangea Season…

The kitchen’s half-clean and I got new barstools! So I’m celebrating. 🥂

We haven’t had barstools in months! (Can you believe Philly sold ours?🤨 Truth: I don’t have a good record with chairs, he sold our kitchen table chairs, too- they all complain that neither were comfortable.)

Barstools are so hard to find! I’ve been looking for over a year!
I finally found these from @chernyshbrothers ✨

“We” wanted something with a low back that would fit under the counter, they needed to be easy in/easy out, well-made, comfortable (and of course, I wanted them to look good!)

These are perfect!
Hand-made, solid oak and 
beautiful quality.  I love the woven natural rope seat and the oak finish is just right!

They are light, comfortable AND…
They passed the test!! We all love them!

I’ve linked them in my #liketoknowit 
(You can follow me there!) 
And I’ll add a swipe up in stories!
#welivehere

#kitchenstyle #kitchenremodel #kitchenisland #kitchendecor #homestyle #homeinspiration #newenglandhome #interiordecorating #hydrangeaseason #hydrangealove #capecodhome #neutraldecor #capecodlifestyle #myhomestyle #homedetails

node.text:
P.S…

When together you have cute initials...you love a monogram.
We go together like “S”alt and “P”epper!💁‍♀️

Now that we are nearly finished with our bedroom suite update, i had to have the most luxurious towels I could find. 
And @matouklinens makes the very best!! 

I love a simple white towel- I chose the Auberge monogram because they are modern and bold, yet subtle and so luxurious! Then I mixed the Kiran waffle towels for texture and together they are the perfect finishing touch!

I love working with local New England companies, @matouklinens has produced quality linens right here in Fall River for 100 years! 

Swipe through to see more details, and I’ve shared my sources in #liketoknowit you can follow me there! I’ll add a swipe up in my stories!

Happy Weekend !! The sun is finally back?🌞

node.text:
Breezy…

There is nothing like summer on Cape Cod! One of my favorite things about living by the coast is the consistent summer breeze off Buzzards Bay.
Our windows are always open and our curtains are always swaying in the breeze.

But one of my least favorite things for my Virgo/ A-type visual-self is to constantly be adjusting them! 😬#ad

When I worked on our bedroom suite window treatments with @TheShadeStore we kept this in mind. 
I wanted a light and airy fabric, unlined so they would move with the breeze. They suggested the Tribeca Track Rod and with pinch pleats on the Luxe Linen drapes. This system would allow the curtains to dance but would give them the structure to fall right back into place perfectly! They would open and close easily and always look great. 

I love waking up to filtered light but wanted the option for privacy. I used a mix of woven wood for privacy and linen for filtered light. Our Luxe Linen Roman Shades on the smaller windows have just a touch of detail, a beautiful mohair bouclé trim!
I love how they are subtle and unfussy yet offer a touch of soft refinement!! Swipe to see! 

We couldn’t be happier with them!

And, working with @TheShadeStore was a breeze😉

So many of you ask for the details:
We used:
•Luxe Linen drapes and Roman Shades (color Beige)
•Roman flat shades in Luxe Linen Beige with Capella Mohair trim (color Sand)
•Waterfall Woven wood shades, Seaview (color Salt)

I’ve shared more details on the blog, linked in bio!

#loveyourwindows #theshadestore #windowtreatments #roomwithaview #sponsored
#roomwithaview #bedroomdecor #myhomestyle

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sandra M Cavallo in Cape Cod with @serenaandlily. May be an image of furniture and living room.

node.text:
Where is Summer…

I spent a long day at Brimfield walking very muddy fields in cloudy, cold weather. It felt like November! #theweatherinnewengland 

Looking forward to a hot shower and curling up right here tonight! After a day like this, there’s no place like home!

I just added a new rug from @serenaandlily ✨
(This the “Carmel”.)

I love how the quiet pattern adds interest but doesn’t interfere with the peaceful feeling of this room! And, it’s such beautiful quality! I’m so excited to share it with you!
#welivehere

node.text:
Current Situation…

We’re about a minute away from “Unruly” so I’m sharing tonight before we start clipping!

(Our Hydrangeas are Endless Summers)

Happy Saturday!💙🌿

(And for all my New England friends: what’s with this weather?🙄)
#welivehere

node.text:
Quick Question…

If you stick a big bunch of Hydrangeas in a jar, does it make doing laundry easier?

It’s taken me all week to dig out from last weekend’s laundry and clean up in here😶.

And, I’m finally seeing the light at the end of the tunnel…
Or maybe that’s Mr. Sunshine finally? (Swipe to see our back hall/mudroom!)

•The little roman shades are from @whitecottageco ✨
•My friend Doug made the cart for me using and old builtin desk from Nathalie’s room.
